 (This PC) or with the Desktop folder itself. The user said \"打开此电脑\" which means opening File Explorer (This PC).\n\nActually, the issue might be that when Explorer opens to \"此电脑\" (This PC / My Computer view), it tries to enumerate drives and also references the Desktop folder for various things. If the Desktop folder path has issues, it can cause Explorer to hang.\n\nLet me suggest a step-by-step fix:\n1. First try: Restart Explorer\n2. Second: Reset Desktop folder location to default\n3. Third: Check for shell extension issues\n\nLet me provide a practical solution. I think the safest fix is to reset the Desktop back to default, and if the user wants files on D: drive, use a different approach.\n\nActually, let me first check if there's a deeper issue. The green progress bar in the address bar is a known Windows bug. Let me try restarting Explorer first, and if that doesn't work, reset the Desktop location.\n\nLet me also check if the Desktop folder has the correct system attribute. Windows Desktop folders should have the ReadOnly attribute (which it does), but they also need to be treated as a system folder. Let me check the desktop.ini content.","signature":"d6462690-9942-45c5-9c2c-56fa8bee881c"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":385,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":33024,"output_tokens":758,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"5bc61d67-5d11-4906-91d4-906b6ab084eb","timestamp":"2026-05-18T02:47:37.245Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"D:\\ClaudeWorkspace","sessionId":"94a964f0-4e4c-4411-a9de-f74c691550d6","version":"2.1.143","gitBranch":"main"}
