{"parentUuid":"a10b188f-ac90-492f-8ce9-9a7bd74cf8d6","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"4f2d2a74-6483-445e-9be6-09d85593774b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All the `$_.` PowerShell expressions got eaten by bash again. Let me write proper script files for the event log checks. But first, the user also added new information: \"左侧的下载变成了：涓嫡浇\" - this is garbled Chinese characters. \"涓嫡浇\" is likely the garbled rendering of \"下载\" (Downloads) in the Explorer navigation pane, indicating the folder name got corrupted.\n\nThis is actually very important! The garbled text \"涓嫡浇\" is a classic symptom of the desktop.ini or folder's LocalizedResourceName being corrupted or pointing to the wrong resource. Let me think...\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully: \"涓嫡浇\" appears in the Explorer left navigation pane where \"下载\" (Downloads) should be. This could be:\n1. The `desktop.ini` in `D:\\下载` having wrong encoding\n2. The folder's localized name registry being corrupted\n3. The folder's desktop.ini having a garbled LocalizedResourceName\n\nBut more importantly, this gives us a new clue about the \"This PC\" hang. If Explorer is trying to resolve the name of a folder and getting garbled/corrupted data, it could hang.\n\nLet me check `D:\\下载\\desktop.ini` and also check the Known Folder definitions.\n\nActually wait - \"涓嫡浇\" - let me think about what this could be. In Windows, when a known folder's name gets corrupted, it usually shows raw characters. \"涓嫡浇\" doesn't look like a typical encoding corruption of \"下载\".\n\nLet me think about other characters:\n- \"下载\" in UTF-8 bytes: E4 B8 8B E8 BD BD\n- If interpreted as GBK/GB2312: 涓 (E4 B8 8B = E4B8 8B... hmm, actually E4B8 in GBK is not standard)\n\nActually, let me not spend too much time decoding this. The key point is the Downloads folder name is garbled, which suggests a deeper corruption issue.\n\nOK, let me take a completely different approach. Let me write comprehensive scripts to files and execute them. This is getting tedious with the bash `$` escaping issue.\n\nActually, let me try the most practical fix at this point. The Downloads fix + cache clearing didn't work. Let me try a more comprehensive approach:\n\n1. First, check the `D:\\下载` desktop.ini\n2. Run a full check of all known folder registrations\n3. Try to fix any issues found\n\nLet me also consider that the issue might NOT be related to the Desktop/Downloads at all. The green progress bar in \"This PC\" is a very common Windows 10 bug that can be caused by:\n1. Windows Search index corruption\n2. A specific Windows Update\n3. Shell extension conflicts\n4. Corrupted icon cache (which we already cleared)\n\nLet me try a completely different fix: disable Windows Search indexing temporarily and see if that helps.\n\nActually, let me try yet another approach. The green progress bar issue is often fixed by:\n1. Opening `services.msc` and restarting the `Windows Search` service\n2. Running `sfc /scannow`\n3. Re-registering shell32.dll\n4. Clearing the `SoftwareDistribution` folder\n\nBut these are all quite invasive. Let me first check the desktop.ini for the Downloads folder and the garbled name issue.\n\nLet me write a comprehensive diagnostic script.","signature":"4f2d2a74-6483-445e-9be6-09d85593774b"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":15017,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":57856,"output_tokens":1309,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"42fbe4f8-6ef7-4d1b-9188-28eafe8a5c71","timestamp":"2026-05-18T03:14:29.352Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"D:\\ClaudeWorkspace","sessionId":"94a964f0-4e4c-4411-a9de-f74c691550d6","ver