e returns False.\n\nThis could mean:\n1. The registry value for Downloads has a slightly different path than `D:\\下载` (e.g., trailing space, different Unicode normalization)\n2. The script file encoding is corrupting the path\n\nLet me try yet another approach: use `cmd /c dir` with ASCII-only paths to verify, or use a PowerShell script that writes all path bytes to a hex dump to check for hidden characters.\n\nActually, let me try the simplest thing: check the actual folder listing of D:\\ and see if \"下载\" exists.\n\nWait, I also noticed the Desktop path from .NET: `D:\\桌面` (D:\\桌面). But the `Test-Path` for the Desktop path worked fine (it found the desktop.ini). So the Desktop path works but Downloads doesn't.\n\nHmm, but the script didn't actually test the Desktop path. It only checked `Join-Path $desktopPath 'desktop.ini'` and found it. This confirms that $desktopPath is valid.\n\nLet me check the raw bytes of the Downloads path from the registry to see if there are any hidden issues.\n\nActually, let me try something much simpler. Let me check if `D:\\下载` exists by listing all directories in D:\\ with a script that uses .NET Directory.GetDirectories().","signature":"2d453e6c-c33a-486d-bd24-4a195fb3e688"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":96,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":81920,"output_tokens":1250,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"4c816600-da4e-459f-b188-751242ebc380","timestamp":"2026-05-18T03:24:16.466Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"D:\\ClaudeWorkspace","sessionId":"94a964f0-4e4c-4411-a9de-f74c691550d6","version":"2.1.143","gitBranch":"main"}
