{"parentUuid":"992a8187-16e5-4fa7-93b6-381306e4ee41","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"336e8717-20a5-4116-a364-7eb71fb33b07","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking a very clear question: they want to understand if it's possible to undo the folder location changes they made (Desktop → D:\\桌面, Downloads → D:\\下载, Documents → E:\\文档) and revert everything back to the way it was before they made those changes.\n\nThey want to know:\n1. Can they undo this action?\n2. If undone, will everything go back to exactly how it was before (files back on C: desktop, etc.)?\n\nThe answer is: Yes, they can undo it using the same method they used to change it - Properties → Location → Restore Default. When you do \"Restore Default\", Windows asks if you want to move all files back to the original location. If you say yes, everything goes back.\n\nBut the user is now in plan mode, so I should NOT execute anything. I should just answer their question and explain clearly.\n\nLet me explain:\n- How to undo: Same method - right-click Desktop on the left nav → Properties → Location → \"Restore Default\" button\n- Windows will ask \"Do you want to move all files from the old location to the new location?\" → Say Yes\n- Everything goes back to C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Desktop (including all files)\n\nThe files currently on D:\\桌面 will be moved back to C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Desktop.\n\nSimilarly for Downloads and Documents.\n\nThis is the cleanest way - using Windows' built-in functionality, not our hacky registry edits.\n\nLet me tell the user this clearly and directly.","signature":"336e8717-20a5-4116-a364-7eb71fb33b07"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1337,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":115072,"output_tokens":531,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1