DIAGNOSTIC COMPLETE\n============================================","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"f1ddeb84-5d15-42a9-832e-74a5c1ee70bd","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"D:\\ClaudeWorkspace","sessionId":"94a964f0-4e4c-4411-a9de-f74c691550d6","version":"2.1.143","gitBranch":"main","slug":"c-d-d-structured-thimble"}
{"parentUuid":"0b8bf25c-c273-40f4-a7ae-0319ec502065","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"e007a5c1-8a22-47eb-89cd-30cc41bca671","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is very revealing! Several important findings:\n\n1. **Baidu Netdisk (百度网盘) namespace extension**: `{679F137C-3162-45da-BE3C-2F9C3D093F64} = 百度网盘` - This adds itself under \"This PC\" and is KNOWN to cause Explorer hangs!\n\n2. **Desktop IShellFolder CLSID MISSING**: `{00021400-0000-0000-C000-000000000046}` is the standard CLSID for the desktop's shell folder. It missing from HKCR is concerning but actually this CLSID is typically registered elsewhere.\n\n3. **Critical shell registry keys MISSING**: `HKCR:\\Folder\\shell`, `HKCR:\\Folder\\shellex`, etc. are missing! This is probably because on 64-bit Windows, these are in a different registry view, or the PowerShell is looking in the wrong place. Let me verify...\n\nActually wait, these \"MISSING\" might be false positives because PowerShell's HKCR: drive maps to the merged view of HKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Classes and HKCU\\SOFTWARE\\Classes. If running as 64-bit PowerShell, HKCR: shows the 64-bit view. Let me check if these keys exist directly at HKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Classes.\n\nBut the MOST IMPORTANT finding is **百度网盘 namespace extension** under MyComputer. This is a well-known cause of Explorer hanging! The Baidu Netdisk client adds a namespace extension that appears as a drive/folder in \"This PC\". If this extension is malfunctioning (which it often does), it will cause the green progress bar to hang indefinitely.\n\nThis would explain:\n- Green bar never completes: Explorer tries to initialize the Baidu Netdisk namespace extension, which hangs\n- White icons: Explorer partially loaded the view but the Baidu Netdisk extension hasn't responded\n- Freeze on click: Explorer is stuck waiting for the hung extension\n\nThe fix would be to remove the Baidu Netdisk namespace extension from MyComputer. This won't uninstall Baidu Netdisk - it just removes its entry from \"This PC\".\n\nBut I need to be careful:\n1. Confirm this is the actual cause\n2. Get user approval before modifying\n\nLet me also check those \"MISSING\" keys to see if they're actually missing or if it's a false positive.\n\nActually, looking at the Baidu Netdisk CLSID: `{679F137C-3162-45da-BE3C-2F9C3D093F64}` - this is a known Baidu Netdisk namespace extension. It appears under \"This PC\" and adds a virtual drive/folder for Baidu cloud storage. When it's not properly connected or authenticated, it can hang Explorer.\n\nBut wait - the user said this problem started right after moving the Desktop folder. Could the Desktop move have triggered something with Baidu Netdisk? Yes, it's possible. When the Desktop folder was moved, Explorer had to rebuild its namespace. If Baidu Netdisk's extension tried to access or reference the Desktop folder during this rebuild and got confused by the moved path, it could now be in a broken state.\n\nThe safest fix: temporarily remove the Baidu Netdisk namespace extension from MyComputer to test if this is the cause. If \"This PC\" starts working, we know Baidu Netdisk is the culprit.\n\nLet me present this finding to the user.","signature":"e007a5c1-8a22-47eb-89cd-30cc41bca671"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1291,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":132608,"output_tokens":890,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"453bbd88-18ae-492c-b2c7-e75a6886c043","timestamp":"2026-05-18T04:32:51.214Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"D:\\ClaudeWorkspace","sessionId":"94a964f0-4e4c-4411-a9de-f74c691550d6","version":"2.1.143","gitBranch":"main","slug":"c-d-d-