{"parentUuid":"3fac0a02-0738-4e9b-856d-c5b87510f421","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"b100e238-00dc-45dd-9532-7dccf6b0f1ff","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so C:\\ and Downloads windows open normally. The problem is ONLY with \"This PC\" view.\n\nThis confirms the issue is specifically with the \"This PC\" namespace (`::{20D04FE0-3AEA-1069-A2D8-08002B30309D}`). \n\n\"This PC\" is built from:\n1. MyComputer\\NameSpace entries (we removed Baidu Netdisk, but there are many others)\n2. The shell's built-in drive enumeration\n\nWait, when the user opens \"This PC,\" the standard view shows:\n- \"Folders\" section: Desktop, Documents, Downloads, Music, Pictures, Videos\n- \"Devices and drives\" section: C:, D:, E:\n\nIf the \"Devices and drives\" section loads fine (we know C:\\, D:\\, E:\\ are all accessible), but the \"Folders\" section or the overall view hangs...\n\nLet me think about this differently. Each entry under MyComputer\\NameSpace is a namespace junction. When Explorer opens \"This PC,\" it enumerates all these junctions and creates shell views for each. If ANY junction's shell implementation hangs (even with a timeout), the green bar will take a long time to complete.\n\nCommon culprits for slow namespace junctions:\n- Network locations that are unavailable\n- MTP/portable device handlers\n- Cloud storage handlers (OneDrive, Dropbox) that need network access\n\nLet me identify what each CLSID is and look for ones that might hang.\n\nLooking at the list:\n- `{24ad3ad4-a569-4530-98e1-ab02f9417aa8}` - This is a known CLSID for... let me think. Actually this is iCloud or iTunes related.\n- `{3dfdf296-dbec-4fb4-81d1-6a3438bcf4de}` - This could be OneDrive or similar\n- `{088e3905-0323-4b02-9826-5d99428e115f}` - This might be OneDrive\n- `{A0953C92-50DC-43bf-BE83-3742FED03C9C}` - OneDrive\n- `{A8CDFF1C-4878-43be-B5FD-F8091C1C60D0}` - Documents namespace\n\nLet me check what these CLSIDs actually are. Let me write a script to identify them all.","signature":"b100e238-00dc-45dd-9532-7dccf6b0f1ff"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":239,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":140928,"output_tokens":1241,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"af820398-ccbb-459f-a91b-7e154f781f20","timestamp":"2026-05-18T04:42:46.645Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"d:\\ClaudeWorkspace","sessionId":"94a964f0-4e4c-4411-a9de-f74c691550d6","version":"2.1.143","gitBranch":"main","slug":"c-d-d-structured-thimble"}
