{"parentUuid":"7cbd1505-526b-461c-ae2e-7d4af8c8471c","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"9adcbcc4-4b49-44f4-9b3e-0a0cbdff0edc","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still the same. Removing Desktop namespace didn't fix it either. So Desktop is not the culprit.\n\nLet me think differently. ALL remaining namespace extensions are standard Windows ones. Yet \"This PC\" hangs. What else could it be?\n\nLet me reconsider. Maybe the problem isn't with MyComputer\\NameSpace at all. Maybe it's with:\n1. The DelegateFolders\n2. The way \"This PC\" enumerates drives\n3. A completely different registry corruption\n4. The drive property handlers\n\nWait - let me re-read the user's description: \"下方有很多文件夹是白色的，不是之前的那种文件夹的图片了\" - the folders below show as WHITE icons. This is important. White icons mean Explorer can't extract icons for those items.\n\nWhen \"This PC\" opens, it shows:\n- The \"Folders\" section (Desktop, Documents, Downloads, etc.)\n- The \"Devices and drives\" section (C:, D:, E:)\n\nIf ALL icons are white (both folders AND drives), the problem is with icon extraction in general. If only folder icons are white, it's specifically with folder icons.\n\nLet me check something: maybe the icon cache is corrupted in a way that clearing files doesn't fix. Windows has an in-memory icon cache that's separate from the on-disk cache files.\n\nActually, let me try a completely different approach. Let me check if the \"This PC\" CLSID itself has issues:\n\n`::{20D04FE0-3AEA-1069-A2D8-08002B30309D}`\n\nThis is the CLSID for \"My Computer\" / \"This PC\". Its shell implementation is in shell32.dll. If this CLSID's registration is corrupted...\n\nLet me check this.\n\nAlso, I want to verify something: when the user opens This PC and it shows white icons, are THOSE white icons the folders (Desktop, Documents, etc.) or are they the drives (C:, D:, E:)? Or both? The user said \"很多文件夹是白色的\" which specifically means folders, not drives.\n\nLet me also try completely resetting the icon cache in a different way. Instead of just deleting cache files, let me:\n1. Kill Explorer\n2. Delete ALL iconcache files  \n3. Use `ie4uinit.exe -ClearIconCache` \n4. Restart Explorer\n\nActually, I want to try something: the problem might be with the Known Folder icon handling. Each known folder (Desktop, Downloads, Documents, etc.) has an icon defined in its desktop.ini. If the icon resource can't be loaded...\n\nWait, the icons come from `%SystemRoot%\\system32\\imageres.dll`. Let me verify this file is intact and accessible.\n\nLet me also try one more thing: completely remove ALL namespace entries from MyComputer (backing them up), restart Explorer, and see if \"This PC\" opens with just drives. If it does, add them back one by one.\n\nActually, that's too aggressive. Let me try removing the DelegateFolders first, since those might be initializing separate shell views.\n\nHmm, but at this point I'm just guessing. Let me try yet another angle.\n\nWhat if the issue is NOT with \"This PC\" at all but with the Windows Explorer itself? The user tried opening \"This PC\" specifically. What if Explorer has a corrupted user profile setting?\n\nLet me try:\n1. Reset the Explorer default view settings\n2. Set Explorer to open to \"This PC\" by default (already the default)\n3. Clear the \"This PC\" specific view settings\n\nActually, let me try something I haven't tried: delete the `HKCU\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Explorer\\Streams` key (after backup). This stores the view layout for various folders including \"This PC\". If it's corrupted...\n\nWait, let me think about what I haven't tried:\n1. ✅ Clear icon cache (deleting files)\n2. ✅ Clear thumbnail cache\n3. ✅ Clear BagMRU and Bags\n4. ✅ Fix folder paths/conflicts\n5. ✅ Fix desktop.ini\n6. ✅ Set ReadOnly on folders\n7. ✅ Remove Baidu Netdisk\n8. ✅ Remove Desktop namespace\n9. ❌ Reset Streams key\n10. ❌ Rebuild icon cache via different method\n11. ❌ Run sfc /scannow\n12. ❌ DISM\n13. ❌ Reboot\n14. ❌ Delete ALL namespace entries\n\nLet me try deleting the Streams key and the Explorer custom view settings. This is safe (Explorer recreates them).\n\nThen if that doesn't work, I'll recommend a reboot.","signature":"9adcbcc4-4b49-44f4-9b3e-0a0cbdff0edc"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":263,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":145792,"output_tokens":1753,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"3a299368-1088-4960-9ffd-6cf21b749b4f","timestamp":"2026-05-18T04:46:00.990Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"d:\\ClaudeWorkspace","sessionId":"94a964f0-4e4c-4411-a9de-f74c691550d6","version":"2.1.143","gitBranch":"main","slug":"c-d-d-structured-thimble"}
